  "body": "# Feature Issue\n\n### User Story\n\nAs a user I want to have easy access to a QRCode scanner, so I don't have to find the right place to scan something.  \n\n### Description\n\nCurrently we have two QRCode scanners, one in chat, and other in the transaction form. It's correct for each of them only accept the types they expect, however it becomes complicated to users if they have to find the right place to scan a QRCode.\n\nOther applications that use multiple QRCode types use only a universal scanner, which recognize the type being scanned and follow the correct path.\n\nFor Status, that would be processing [ERC-681] and other future [ERC-831], this universal scanner would be important.\n\nOther modifications would have to be made, such as the public chats, private chats, and more follow a standard format, so it can be decoded by the scanner more easily.\n\nWithout falling into [ERC-831], scanning;\n- `#channel`: a public channel; \n- `@0x\"68 byte long number\"`: a pubkey (private chat); \n- `@anything.eth`: resolve a pubkey (private chat); \n- `anything.eth`: resolve a [ERC-1577] in browser (dapp). \n\nFalling into [ERC-831] we could have also:\n`ethereum:pay-`: [ERC-681], opens payment wall with default account;\n`ethereum:tx-`: [ERC-2400], checks and display transaction (offer link to view in etherscan).\n\nAfter scanning, the data should be rendered (when possible) and user must be asked if want to follow the scanned action (never autorun on scan), which the rendering would help in user decision.  \n\n### Notes\n\nThe list of [ERC-831] should grow. A discussion was open to standardize all deep links in Status under this standard, see https://discuss.status.im/t/eip831-uri-format-for-ethereum-in-status/1402\n\n[ERC-831]: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-831\n[ERC-681]: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-681\n[ERC-1577]: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1577\n[ERC-2400]: https://github.com/status-im/EIPs/blob/tx-hash-uri/EIPS/eip-2400.md",
